00:38:44.711 --> 00:38:47.210
So you can just squeeze sugar
cane, have you ever tasted it?

00:38:47.210 --> 00:38:48.810
It's delicious just like that.

00:38:48.810 --> 00:38:51.080
It's not super sweet,
it's just really good.

00:38:51.080 --> 00:38:53.450
And you can distill that,
make a Rhum Agricole.

00:38:53.450 --> 00:38:55.810
It's a product that
got made in a lot

00:38:55.810 --> 00:38:58.520
of the former French
colonies in South America

00:38:58.520 --> 00:38:59.830
and in the Caribbean.

00:38:59.830 --> 00:39:00.641
You can find them.

00:39:00.641 --> 00:39:01.390
They're delicious.

00:39:01.390 --> 00:39:05.080
They're really interesting, they
smell kind of funky and grassy.

00:39:05.080 --> 00:39:09.220
And if you're making
moonshine-- famously moonshine

00:39:09.220 --> 00:39:11.500
is whiskey, un-aged whiskey.

00:39:11.500 --> 00:39:14.760
But like cheap moonshine--
especially present day,

00:39:14.760 --> 00:39:17.370
cheap, illegal
moonshine-- is often

00:39:17.370 --> 00:39:20.380
like they go buy a lot of sugar,
ferment that, and distill it.

00:39:20.380 --> 00:39:21.730
Or they use any sugar substrate.

00:39:21.730 --> 00:39:25.580
I've seen a mash
