before going to work that
day to try to come back.

00:43:14.580 --> 00:43:16.402
So that's hair of the dog.

00:43:16.402 --> 00:43:17.860
The idea is that
if you're hungover

00:43:17.860 --> 00:43:18.880
you have a little bit
of booze, and that

00:43:18.880 --> 00:43:20.546
makes you not feel
the hangover anymore.

00:43:20.546 --> 00:43:22.820
So probably all it does is
just delay the hangover,

00:43:22.820 --> 00:43:24.740
because you're more
relaxed about it.

00:43:24.740 --> 00:43:25.710
But there is a theory.

00:43:25.710 --> 00:43:28.177
I mentioned methanol toxicity.

00:43:28.177 --> 00:43:30.510
There is a theory that says
that a hangover are actually

00:43:30.510 --> 00:43:34.380
the symptoms of a very, very,
small amount of methanol.

00:43:34.380 --> 00:43:36.390
So methanol's really cool.

00:43:36.390 --> 00:43:38.190
It's a different alcohol.

00:43:38.190 --> 00:43:40.620
And alcohol
dehydrogenase-- we all

00:43:40.620 --> 00:43:42.200
make that too,
that's how we process

00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:46.240
alcohol in our own bodies--
will work on methanol also.

00:43:46.240 --> 00:43:49.880
But instead of
having ethanol, which

00:43:49.880 --> 00:43:52.190
it can change into
acetaldehyde aldehyde

00:43:52.190 --> 00:43:54.260
in us, when it
works on methanol,

00:43:54.260 --> 00:43:58.952
it changes it into
formaldehyde, which is bad.

00:43:58.952 --> 00:44:01.160
Doesn't last long in the
body, it's not good for you,

00:44:01.160 --> 00:44:03.040
but it kind of goes away.

00:44:03.040 --> 00:44:05.400
But it turns into
formic acid, which

00:44:05.400 --> 00:44:07.570
is the stuff in ant venom.

00:44:07.570 --> 00:44:10.130
So you get acidosis.

00:44:10.130 --> 00:44:11.900
Formic acid interferes
with the enzyme

00:44:11.900 --> 00:44:14.620
that we use to process
oxygen in our cells.

00:44:14.620 --> 00:44:17.810
So the heaviest oxygen
users in our body

00:44:17.810 --> 00:44:19.890
are the eyes and the brain.

00:44:19.890 --> 00:44:21.759
That's why when you
have oxygen deprivation

00:44:21.759 --> 00:44:24.050
the first thing that happens
is you stop seeing colors.

00:44:24.050 --> 00:44:26.050
And then you get
that tunnel that

00:44:26.050 --> 00:44:27.900
closes in when
you're not breathing.

00:44:30.447 --> 00:44:32.530
Formic acid messes with
the enzyme that does that.

00:44:32.530 --> 00:44:34.450
It's why methanol toxicity
will make you go blind.

00:44:34.450 --> 00:44:37.120
And eventually it goes into the
brain, messes with the brain's

00:44:37.120 --> 00:44:39.529
ability to deal with oxygen,
you get Parkinsonian tremor.

00:44:39.529 --> 00:44:40.570
Eventually, it kills you.

00:44:40.570 --> 00:44:43.080
But if you show up in an
emergency room with methanol

00:44:43.080 --> 00:44:46.282
toxicity, not that
I'm recommending this,

00:44:46.282 --> 00:44:47.740
the first thing
the doctors will do

00:44:47.740 --> 00:44:49.656
is they will give you a
giant dose of ethanol.

00:44:49.656 --> 00:44:52.836
Because ethanol displaces
the methanol off the enzyme.

00:44:52.836 --> 00:44:54.710
The enzyme would much
rather work on ethanol.

00:44:54.710 --> 00:44:57.052
They hit you with the
ethanol, the enzyme

00:44:57.052 --> 00:44:59.510
throws the methanol overboard,
goes to work on the ethanol,

00:44:59.510 --> 00:45:01.551
and you excrete the methanol
through your breath,

00:45:01.551 --> 00:45:02.350
and you pee it out.

00:45:02.350 --> 00:45:04.110
Basically, that's
the therapy for it.

00:45:04.110 --> 00:45:08.560
So the notion is if a
hangover is methanol toxicity,

00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:10.070
you're going to
have another drink,

00:45:10.070 --> 00:45:13.119
the ethanol will displace
the methanol off the enzyme,

00:45:13.119 --> 00:45:14.160
and you will feel better.

00:45:14.160 --> 00:45:17.590
That's the theory--
that's the hypothesis,

00:45:17.590 --> 00:45:18.650
nobody's proved that.

00:45:18.650 --> 00:45:22.280
It's a great just-so story.

00:45:22.280 --> 00:45:24.030
