yeast to do other stuff.

00:53:59.980 --> 00:54:02.610
So there's a
researcher in Australia

00:54:02.610 --> 00:54:06.280
named Isaac Pretorius,
and he worked on a yeast

00:54:06.280 --> 00:54:09.740
that-- I'm going to radically
simplify this, I'm sorry,

00:54:09.740 --> 00:54:10.530
this is terrible.

00:54:10.530 --> 00:54:14.450
Basically, it would take crummy
grapes and make decent wine.

00:54:14.450 --> 00:54:17.079
Because it was able to break
a particular molecular bond

00:54:17.079 --> 00:54:18.620
that was liberating
a flavor that you

00:54:18.620 --> 00:54:20.620
wanted in Sauvignon blanc
that they were growing

00:54:20.620 --> 00:54:23.990
in too hot a climate for
Sauvignon blanc, essentially.

00:54:23.990 --> 00:54:26.060
There's a woman in France
named Sylvie Dequin,

00:54:26.060 --> 00:54:27.920
and she's working
on yeasts that will

00:54:27.920 --> 00:54:30.950
make wine that tastes good,
but has lower alcohol levels.

00:54:30.950 --> 00:54:33.310
You might know this, but
especially in California wines,

00:54:33.310 --> 00:54:34.471
alcohol, ABV's creeping up.

00:54:34.471 --> 00:54:36.970
Because the yeast that they're
using and the process they're

00:54:36.970 --> 00:54:37.800
using is more efficient.

00:54:37.800 --> 00:54:39.591
They're getting more
alcohol off the sugar.

00:54:39.591 --> 00:54:41.130
So you end up with
wine that used

00:54:41.130 --> 00:54:45.580
to be 8%, 9%, you can get it
at 15, which is super high.

00:54:45.580 --> 00:54:48.400
And it does-- I mean it's
a flavor that people like,

00:54:48.400 --> 00:54:52.505
but also you're blitzed
on a glass of wine.

00:54:52.505 --> 00:54:54.380
So she's working on
yeast that won't do that.

00:54:54.380 --> 00:54:55.670
You still get the flavor,
but not the alcohol.

00:54:55.670 --> 00:54:58.030
Of course nobody in the
world-- I shouldn't say that.

00:54:58.030 --> 00:55:01.157
If you have a GMO yeast,
you can't sell it in Europe.

00:55:01.157 --> 00:55:03.740
And you'd have trouble selling
it here, you'd get controversy.

00:55:03.740 --> 00:55:07.392
So after Pretorius
made that yeast,

00:55:07.392 --> 00:55:09.600
once he knew which genes it
was, he went back and did

00:55:09.600 --> 00:55:16.810
it standard breeding, he grew
a strain up without genetically

00:55:16.810 --> 00:55:19.170
modifying it and he sells that.

00:55:19.170 --> 00:55:22.329
So there's room in the
yeast, to mess with yeast

00:55:22.329 --> 00:55:23.620
